msgid "Configuring Mattermost"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:69
msgid ""
"On the Mattermost server, open the file ``config.json`` and look for the "
"``DataSource`` value in the ``SqlSettings`` section. It should look "
"similar to this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:72
msgid ""
"``\"DataSource\": "
"\"mmuser:sad09zusaopdhsad123@tcp(10.10.250.148:3306)/mattermost?charset=utf8mb4,utf8\\u0026readTimeout=30s\\u0026writeTimeout=30s\",``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:74
msgid ""
"At the end of the line, we can configure that TLS must be turned on with "
"the ``tls`` flag which supports the following values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:77
msgid "true (Require TLS + a trusted certificate)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:78
msgid "false"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:79
msgid "skip-verify (Require TLS + accept self-signed)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:80
msgid "preferred (Try TLS, fallback to unencrypted)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:82
msgid ""
"In our case we need to use ``skip-verify`` since we use a self-signed "
"certificate. The configuration setting will now look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:85
msgid ""
"``\"DataSource\": "
"\"mmuser:sad09zusaopdhsad123@tcp(10.10.250.148:3306)/mattermost?charset=utf8mb4,utf8\\u0026readTimeout=30s\\u0026writeTimeout=30s&tls"
"=skip-verify\",``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/transport-encryption/config-database.rst:87
msgid ""
"If you are running Mattermost in a cluster, be sure to update the value "
"on each node of the cluster. If you are using configuration in the "
"database, be sure to update the ``systemd`` unit file and enable TLS for "
"the configuration store."
msgstr ""

